make_cast.description:
Make a Transformation that casts a vector of data from type `TIA` to type `TOA`. 
Failure to parse results in None, else Some<TOA>.

args.name: TIA
args.description: atomic input data type to cast from

args.name: TOA
args.description: atomic data type to cast into

make_cast_default.description: Make a Transformation that casts a vector of data from type `TIA` to type `TOA`. If cast fails, fill with default.

args.name: TIA
args.description: atomic input data type to cast from

args.name: TOA
args.description: atomic data type to cast into

make_is_equal.description: Make a Transformation that checks if each element is equal to `value`.

args.name: value
args.description: value to check against

args.name: TIA
args.description: atomic input data type

make_is_null.description: Make a Transformation that checks if each element in a vector is null.

args.name: DIA
args.description: atomic input domain

make_cast_inherent.description:
Make a Transformation that casts a vector of data from type `TI` to a type that can represent nullity `TO`. 
If cast fails, fill with `TO`'s null value.

args.name: TIA
args.description: input data type to cast from

args.name: TOA
args.description: data type to cast into

make_cast_metric.description: Make a Transformation that converts the dataset metric from type `MI` to type `MO`.

args.name: MI
args.description: input dataset metric

args.name: MO
args.description: output dataset metric

args.name: TA
args.description: atomic type of data

make_clamp.description:
Make a Transformation that clamps numeric data in Vec<`T`> to `bounds`. 
If datum is less than lower, let datum be lower. 
If datum is greater than upper, let datum be upper.

args.name: bounds
args.description: Tuple of inclusive lower and upper bounds.

args.name: TA
args.description: atomic data type

make_unclamp.description: Make a Transformation that unclamps a VectorDomain<BoundedDomain<T>> to a VectorDomain<AllDomain<T>>.

args.name: bounds
args.description: Tuple of inclusive lower and upper bounds.

args.name: TA
args.description: atomic data type

make_count.description: Make a Transformation that computes a count of the number of records in data.

args.name: TIA
args.description: Atomic Input Type. Input data is expected to be of the form Vec<TIA>.

args.name: TO
args.description: Output Type. Must be numeric.

make_count_distinct.description: Make a Transformation that computes a count of the number of unique, distinct records in data.

args.name: TIA
args.description: Atomic Input Type. Input data is expected to be of the form Vec<TIA>.

args.name: TO
args.description: Output Type. Must be numeric.

make_count_by.description:
Make a Transformation that computes the count of each unique value in data. 
This assumes that the category set is unknown. 
This uses a restricted-sensitivity proof that takes advantage of known dataset size. 
Use `make_resize` to establish dataset size. 
This transformation depends on a measurement that has not yet been implemented.

args.name: size
args.description: Number of records in input data.

args.name: MO
args.description: Output Metric.

args.name: TIA
args.description: Atomic Input Type. Categorical/hashable input data type. Input data must be Vec<TI>.

args.name: TOA
args.description: Atomic Output Type. Express counts in terms of this integral type.

ret.description: The carrier type is HashMap<TI, TO>- the counts for each unique data input.

make_count_by_categories.description:
Make a Transformation that computes the number of times each category appears in the data. 
This assumes that the category set is known.

args.name: categories
args.description: The set of categories to compute counts for.

args.name: MO
args.description: output sensitivity metric

args.name: TIA
args.description: categorical/hashable input type. Input data must be Vec<TIA>.

args.name: TOA
args.description: express counts in terms of this numeric type

make_split_lines.description: Make a Transformation that takes a string and splits it into a Vec<String> of its lines.

make_split_records.description: Make a Transformation that splits each record in a Vec<String> into a Vec<Vec<String>>.

args.name: separator
args.description: The token(s) that separate entries in each record.

make_create_dataframe.description: Make a Transformation that constructs a dataframe from a Vec<Vec<String>>.

args.name: col_names
args.description: Column names for each record entry.

args.name: K
args.description: categorical/hashable data type of column names

make_split_dataframe.description:
Make a Transformation that splits each record in a String into a Vec<Vec<String>>,
and loads the resulting table into a dataframe keyed by `col_names`.

args.name: separator
args.description: The token(s) that separate entries in each record.

args.name: col_names
args.description: Column names for each record entry.

args.name: K
args.description: categorical/hashable data type of column names

make_select_column.description: Make a Transformation that retrieves the column `key` from a dataframe as Vec<`TOA`>.

args.name: key
args.description: categorical/hashable data type of the key/column name

args.name: K
args.description: data type of the key

args.name: TOA
args.description: atomic data type to downcast to

make_identity.description: Make a Transformation that simply passes the data through.

args.name: D
args.description: Domain of the identity function. Must be VectorDomain<AllDomain<_>> or AllDomain<_>

args.name: M
args.description: metric. Must be a dataset metric if D is a VectorDomain or a sensitivity metric if D is an AllDomain

ret.description: A transformation where the input and output domain are D and the input and output metric are M

make_impute_constant.description:
Make a Transformation that replaces null/None data with `constant`.
By default, the input type is Vec<Option<TA>>, as emitted by make_cast. 
Set `DA` to InherentNullDomain<AllDomain<TA>> for imputing on types that have an inherent representation of nullity, like floats.

args.name: constant
args.description: Value to replace nulls with.

args.name: DA
args.description: domain of data being imputed. This is OptionNullDomain<AllDomain<TA>> or InherentNullDomain<AllDomain<TA>>

make_drop_null.description: Make a Transformation that drops null values.

args.name: DA
args.description: atomic domain of input data that contains nulls. This is OptionNullDomain<AllDomain<TA>> or InherentNullDomain<AllDomain<TA>>

make_impute_uniform_float.description: Make a Transformation that replaces null/None data in Vec<`TA`> with uniformly distributed floats within `bounds`.

args.name: bounds
args.description: Tuple of inclusive lower and upper bounds.

args.name: TA
args.description: type of data being imputed

make_find.description: Find the index of a data value in a set of categories.

args.name: categories
args.description: The set of categories to find indexes from.

args.name: TIA
args.description: categorical/hashable input type. Input data must be Vec<TIA>.

make_find_bin.description: Find the bin index from a monotonically increasing vector of edges.

args.name: edges
args.description: The set of edges to split bins by.

args.name: TIA
args.description: numerical input type. Input data must be Vec<TIA>.

make_index.description: Index into a vector of categories.

args.name: categories
args.description: The set of categories to index into.

args.name: null
args.description: Category to return if the index is out-of-range of the category set.

args.name: TOA
args.description: atomic output type. Output data will be Vec<TIA>.

make_sized_bounded_mean.description:
Make a Transformation that computes the mean of bounded data. 
This uses a restricted-sensitivity proof that takes advantage of known dataset size. 
Use `make_clamp` to bound data and `make_bounded_resize` to establish dataset size.

args.name: size
args.description: Number of records in input data.

args.name: bounds
args.description: Tuple of inclusive lower and upper bounds of the input data.

args.name: T
args.description: atomic data type

make_resize.description: Make a Transformation that either truncates or imputes records with `constant` in a Vec<`TA`> to match a provided `size`.

args.name: size
args.description: Number of records in output data.

args.name: constant
args.description: Value to impute with.

args.name: TA
args.description: Atomic type.

ret.description: A vector of the same type `TA`, but with the provided `size`.

make_bounded_resize.description: Make a Transformation that either truncates or imputes records with `constant` in a Vec<`TA`> to match a provided `size`.

args.name: size
args.description: Number of records in output data.

args.name: bounds
args.description: Tuple of lower and upper bounds for data in the input domain

args.name: constant
args.description: Value to impute with.

args.name: TA
args.description: Atomic type. If not passed, TA is inferred from the lower bound.

ret.description: A vector of the same type `TA`, but with the provided `size`.

make_bounded_sum.description:
Make a Transformation that computes the sum of bounded data. 
Use `make_clamp` to bound data.

args.name: bounds
args.description: Tuple of lower and upper bounds for data in the input domain

args.name: T
args.description: atomic type of data

make_sized_bounded_sum.description:
Make a Transformation that computes the sum of bounded data with known dataset size. 
This uses a restricted-sensitivity proof that takes advantage of known dataset size for better utility. 
Use `make_clamp` to bound data and `make_bounded_resize` to establish dataset size.

args.name: size
args.description: Number of records in input data.

args.name: bounds
args.description: Tuple of lower and upper bounds for input data

args.name: T
args.description: atomic type of data

make_sized_bounded_variance.description:
Make a Transformation that computes the variance of bounded data. 
This uses a restricted-sensitivity proof that takes advantage of known dataset size. 
Use `make_clamp` to bound data and `make_bounded_resize` to establish dataset size.

args.name: size
args.description: Number of records in input data.

args.name: bounds
args.description: Tuple of lower and upper bounds for input data

args.name: ddof
args.description: Delta degrees of freedom. Set to 0 if not a sample, 1 for sample estimate.

args.name: T
args.description: atomic data type
